Durban - Pietermaritzburg security guard Nkosiphile Ndlovu, linked to the alleged kidnapping of Sikhumbuzo Mjwara, the owner of uMhlanga’s upmarket Barrio Restaurant made a brief appearance in Verulam Magistrate's Court, on Friday morning. Ndlovu,39, was arrested on Thursday by members of the provincial police task team. He is the third person that has been arrested for the alleged kidnapping. All three men were arrested in Pietermaritzburg. Two policemen -Sergeant Thabane Cyril Ndlovu and Constable Collen Makhaye- both 37, and Ndlovu will formally apply for bail on October 15. Mjwara was kidnapped outside the Verulam Magistrate's Court on August 30. The businessman has not been found. He was reported missing by his wife, according to police spokesperson Lt Colonel Thulani Zwane. The family declined to comment to the Sunday Tribune fearing for Mjwara's safety. Zwane confirmed all three arrests. All three men are being held at Verulam SAPS until their next court appearance. Daily News